## CSS Variables and Custom Properties

- **Color variables**: Use CSS variables for colors (--chords, --scales, --play, --background, --black, --white, --orange, --green, --blue)
- **Page-specific colors**: Each page has its own color variable (--chords, --scales, --play)
- **Theme consistency**: Maintain consistent use of CSS variables throughout the application
- **Custom classes**: Use custom CSS classes for page-specific styling (Chords, Scales, Play)

### CSS Variable Usage

```css
/* In globals.css */
:root {
	--black: #000000;
	--orange: #ffb86a;
	--green: #64f58d;
	--blue: #74d4ff;
	--white: #ffffff;

	--chords: var(--orange);
	--scales: var(--blue);
	--play: var(--green);
	--background: var(--white);
}

.Chords {
	background-color: var(--chords);
}

.Scales {
	background-color: var(--scales);
}

.Play {
	background-color: var(--play);
}
```

```tsx
// In components - use custom CSS classes that reference CSS variables
<Main componentName='Chords'>
	{/* Chords class applies --chords background color */}
</Main>

// Direct CSS variable usage when needed
<div style={{ backgroundColor: 'var(--chords)' }}>
	{/* Direct variable access */}
</div>
```

## Custom CSS Patterns

- **Page-specific styling**: Custom CSS classes for page-specific background colors (Chords, Scales, Play)
- **Button styles**: Custom CSS for button component with hover states
- **Component-specific**: Use custom CSS classes for complex or reusable patterns
- **CSS organization**: Keep custom CSS in `globals.css` organized by component/pattern

### Custom CSS Examples

