## CSS Best Practices

- **No !important**: Avoid using `!important` declarations in CSS
- **TypeScript**: Avoid using the `any` type in TypeScript code
- **Semantic HTML**: Use semantic HTML elements for better accessibility (header, main, nav, section, etc.)
- **Responsive design**: Use Tailwind responsive prefixes (sm:, md:, lg:, xl:)
- **Custom classes**: Use custom CSS classes for page-specific styling (Chords, Scales, Play)
- **CSS organization**: Organize CSS by component/pattern, keep related styles together in globals.css
- **Transitions**: Use CSS transitions for smooth state changes (e.g., hover states, active states)
